                    <h4>What is this?</h4>
                    <ul class="TfDdl">
                        <li>A map of Canada and La Nouvelle France</li>

                        <li>An original 1755 document on parchment</li>

                        <li>A display of where the Native American tribes were located in 1755</li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>How did we get this map?</h4>
                    <p>It was purchased based on the information in the inventory of Louis Bolduc’s property after the death of his second wife, Agatha Govreau. The National Society of the Colonial Dames of America in the State of Missouri funded its acquisition in 1957 </p>

                    <h4>Does it need any special care or restoration?</h4>
                    <ul class="TfDdl">
                        <li>It was archivally framed several years ago</li>
                        <li>There is some damage from where our interpreters used a pointer to locate Ste. Genevieve
                                            on the map</li>
                        <li>It is difficult for visitors to read easily because the Bolduc House Museum has
                                            an inadequate lighting system</li>
                    </ul>


                    <h4>What is important about the map?</h4>
                    <ul class="TfDdl">
                        <li>It was drawn by D’Anville, the most prolific cartographer of Louis XV. He never
                                            left Paris so to draw the map D;Anville required really good technical communication
                                            skills from the explorers.</li>

                        <li>The longitude notation uses a prime meridian different from Greenwich, England. 
                        </li>
                        <li>It shows Ste. Genevieve, Kaskaskia, and Cahokia but not St. Louis. </li>
                        <li>It is centered on Washington. D.C.  </li>
                    </ul>
                    <h4>What inaccuracies are there on this map?</h4>
                    <ul class="TfDdl">
                        <li>Lake Michigan should not be due north of the Florida peninsula. 
                        </li>
                        <li>Lake Michigan is too little. </li>
                    </ul>

